levels.message: It is slow and inefficient, but it’s built from parts supposed to be working. Whatever that means.
Changing the chips for better parts, hoping for some performance gain.
Oh no, we made it worse. Can't be that bad, right?
This sound chip is much better, but messes with the video signal.
Make it faster, no matter the cost.
We're going too fast, stability is compromised.
Let's see what we can build out of our best parts.
Speed improvements galore, but what about video clarity?
Opening horizons, let's try improving the graphics, somehow.
We're approaching weird territory. But it looks so cool.
Let's see what we can build out of our best parts.
I don't feel so good, the walls are spinning.
Would it look better on an old laptop from the 90s ?
Let's push the console to its limits. Make the graphics look modern and clean. (This does not work with every game)
